Linux is a family of open-source Unix-like operating systems based on the Linux kernel, 
an operating system kernel first released on September 17, 1991, by Linus Torvalds.

Linux is used in the following ways: 
Server OS for web servers, 
database servers, 
file servers, 
email servers and any other type of shared server. 

Designed to support high-volume and multithreading applications, 
Linux is well-suited for all types of server applications.
